content: Yes, the UK has signed trade agreements with several major trading partners. For instance, the UK signed a comprehensive free trade agreement with the European Union, which is its largest trading partner. Additionally, the UK has signed trade deals with countries such as Japan, Canada, and South Korea. These are some of the largest economies in the world, and these agreements have helped to secure trade continuity and reduce uncertainty for businesses. However, it is worth noting that trade negotiations are ongoing with some countries, including the United States and Australia, and the details of these agreements are subject to change.
